    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@dhermes This behavior difference is likely due to an inherent problem with `manylinux` binary wheels. `manylinux` platform, for which we distribute binaries, emulates a very old Linux version and does not support the system calls required for more advanced polling strategies, thereby falling back to simple `poll` syscall. I don't think there's much that can be done here for the behavior difference of `poll`-fallback. The particular bug itself, of course, will hopefully get fixed, but I don't think there's much (or at least anything trivial) we can do to activate `epoll` on `manylinux` (Ideas welcome!).\r\n\r\nYou can try forcing the `GRPC_POLL_STRATEGY=poll` environment variable on your built-from-source version and see if it manifests the problem to confirm my strong suspicion.\r\n  "
  },
